notes.body:
Genome-scale metabolic model of synthetic bacterium JCVI-Syn3A
Constructed by (Breuer et al. 2019) based on JCVI-Syn3A (NCBI accession, CP016816.2, Direct Submission: Glass, 2016-2018).
Sythetic organism JCVI-Syn3A results from genome optimiztion of JCVI-syn3.0 (Hutchison at al, 2016) with the aim to restore morphological features and increase growth rate as discribed in Breuer et al. 2019..
The SBML model has been further annotated by Peter Schubert, using information from original submision (Breuer et al. 2019) and extracted from databases. Annotation data can subsequently be used in creating enzyme, resource balance and thermodymanics constraint models.
